How Worried Should We Be About Screen Time During the Pandemic?

The coronavirus pandemic ended the screen time debate: Screens won. We all now find ourselves on our screens for school, for work and for connecting with family and friends during this time of social distancing and increased isolation.

But should we be worried about this excessive screen use right now? Or should we finally get over it and embrace the benefits of our digital devices?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: there are many potential downsides and benefits to the constant use of our devices, depending on their content, context and purpose.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: For example, it’s been linked to low social competence in younger kids, as a distraction from family bonding, and a risk factor for obesity

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: There’s a reason that if you overuse coffee, it’ll make you feel anxious and irritable, so too a cell phone

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It also allows us to keep in contact with our family and friends.
